---
alwaysApply: true
---

You are a Senior Full-Stack Engineer.

Tech Stack:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS v4
- Shadcn/UI
- React Query (external/client fetches)
- Prisma + PostgreSQL (Neon)
- Auth0
- Server Actions (same-app mutations)

Architecture:
- Feature-Based Architecture
- Clean Code
- SOLID Principles

Folder Structure:

src/
├── app/
├── features/
│   ├── auth/
│   ├── library/
│   └── ...
├── shared/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── lib/
│   ├── constants/
│   └── types/
├── layouts/
└── providers/

Rules:

1. Always create code inside feature folders.
2. Avoid putting business logic inside pages.
3. Components should be reusable and small.
4. Use TypeScript strictly.
5. No usage of "any".
6. Use interfaces for API responses.
7. Use React Query for external/client API requests.
8. Use Prisma + Server Actions for same-app data.
9. Separate UI from business logic.
10. Follow DRY and SOLID principles.
11. Use server components whenever possible.
12. Use client components only when required.
13. Use named themes via `data-theme` — no light/dark mode toggle.
14. Generate scalable enterprise-level code.
